cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on recurrent neural networks and their backpropagation algorithm. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the training of RNNs using error backpropagation. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as RNNs are commonly used in natural language processing tasks such as speech recognition and language translation. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as RNNs have also been applied to image captioning and video analysis tasks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a broad category that could also apply as RNNs are a popular tool in many AI applications.
